SUMMARY:RadMedic Animals and Insects Workshop
LOCATION:1963 Ontario E
DESCRIPTION:2026-07-25 16:00:00\n\n1963 Ontario E\n\nhttps://www.openstree
 tmap.org/node/11108904490\n\nRadMedic Animals and Insects&nbsp\;Workshop\n
 07/25\, 4-6pm\, Black Flag Combat Club (1963 rue Ontario E)\n&nbsp\;\nRadM
 edic is a network of street and protest medics that host weekly first aid 
 workshops and trainings relevant to the environments we medic in. This mea
 ns that we are acutely aware that care is politicized\; withheld from thos
 e who are not deemed worthy by the state\, and provided on the condition t
 hat one obeys and maintains the status quo. Our main goal is to share firs
 t aid knowledge (outside of expensive certification programs!) so that we 
 can all feel confident in responding to injuries or emergencies around us.
  In our trainings\, expect a learning component and a practice component (
 usually in the form of scenario simulations) that meet everyone where they
 're at — from experienced medic to absolute beginner.\n&nbsp\;\nThe Anim
 als and Insects Workshop focuses on common insects and animal risks found 
 in Montreal. For the insect portion\, we'll be going over common insects f
 ound in the city\, their various levels of injuries and additional concern
 s\, and ways to identify and treat them. For the animal portion\, we'll re
 view how to treat animal based injuries\, focusing on bites and scratches 
 from mammals\, differences between domesticated and wild animals\, and whe
 n to go to a hospital.\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/11108904490
END:VEVENT
